episodes.title: TopDATA Global IT Solutions
episodes.description:
A lot of BPOs in the Philippines can offer you a job, but what if you’re looking for more—what if you want to build a career?

Consider TopData Global IT Solutions, a premiere BPO located in Angeles. The company has spent over a decade helping customers around the globe, providing outstanding non-voice technical support. 

At TopData, employees are the secret to success. They combine amazing people skills with technical capabilities to deliver the best support in the industry. 

Where does the enthusiasm come from?

TopData is not just focused on offering top-notch customer support. With one of the lowest employee turnover rates in the BPO industry, TopData is committed to offering a stress-free work environment.

There’s never a dull moment at TopData. The office offers plenty of ways for employees to relax, have fun, and get to know one another. 

With such a strong office community, it’s no surprise that agents stay with TopData for many years. Many even rise up the ranks and manage new recruits. 

Wonderful opportunities and high pay make TopData a top choice for workers in the BPO industry. As a result, the interview process is highly selective. But persistence can pay off. 

Are you looking for something out of the ordinary? Are you looking for a work team that feels like family and is there for you year after year?

TopData is actively growing, and we’re seeking tech support specialists from all backgrounds. 

Maybe it’s time you applied!

episodes.title: Hugot Radio Ad - Midweek Marketing with Timothy Black
episodes.description:
Hugot Radio is arguably the best easy listening online station in the Philippines! 

I am inviting you to promote your podcast for a minimal fee on my Online Radio. I call it Hugot Radio. We play the best easy listening music 24/7. With more than 9000 Fans on Facebook and counting!

Information:

Hugot (pronounced as Who-Goat)

Definition: "Hugot" is a Filipino slang which literally means "drawn from a deep place" and figuratively means "deeply emotional". Usually words with potentially and personally deep sentimental or emotional undertones. Because feelings come from "deep within" so you have had to "hugot" your emotions first "from deep within" before you would've actually blurted them out in somehow emotionally undertoned words — subconsciously or otherwise.

This online radio is fairly new but it is now attracting listeners mostly from  countries like:
Philippines, Saudi Arabia, Japan, United States, Morocco, Latvia, Canada, Mexico, Norway, S. Korea, Netherlands, Kuwait, Qatar, Germany, Singapore, Australia, UK, UAE and more!

Website: http://bit.ly/HugotRadio
Facebook: http://bit.ly/HugotRadioFB

episodes.title: Timothy Black of Midweek Marketing Podcast
episodes.description:
Online Marketing News and Information. New episodes every Tuesday and Thursday.

Midweeek Marketing is a twice-weekly podcast produced by Timothy Black. Each episode you'll discover ways to improve your online marketing, whether you're a small business owner trying to figure out this whole intermnet marketing thing, or someone looking to start a digital agency helping small businesses AKA "offline marketing." Tim will show you the best ways to reach new clients, improve costs, how to sell services and how to talk to past customers so they continue to buy from you. We have a LOT to cover so new episodes go up every Tuesday and Thursday. But don't worry, it's short and to the point. Each episode is only about 15 minutes. We'll be talking about everything from Facebook Ads to Website creation to SEO, PPC, email marketing and even how to generate new leads from social media platforms like Twitter, LinkedIn, Pinterest, Instagram, Snapchat, Busker and more. In an ever changing digital marketing landscape, Midweek Marketing is your source for all the latest online marketing news. 

Visit http://midweekmarketing.com/

episodes.title: Emma Franklin Bell's Testimonial of The Ladies Lounge
episodes.description:
Anna Massie and Emma Franklin Bell invite you into The Ladies Lounge to listen in as guests confess the truth and reveal what made them want to be their own boss and what drove them to jump ship from the life they were living into the often daunting and unpredictable road less travelled - entrepreneurial life.

In up-close-and-personal candid conversations, inspirational and empowering ladies (and some lads) uncover the raw truth behind their business and their beginnings.

Emma and Anna ask those penetrating questions we all want to ask like what was the catalyst for making the shift to business? What were the breakthroughs and sometimes breakdowns that got you to where you are now? And how have you faced your fears and broken through them?

This riveting and thrilling show dissects and dares to open up about the life you create as a modern-day lady in business and how the integration and harmonious intersection of life and business is now paving the way for the new wave of women in business.
